      "source": [
        "# Structural and Readability Metrics for Chatbot Responses\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook calculates structural, formatting, and readability metrics for chatbot responses from your dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "**IMPORTANT: This version does NOT clean or modify the response text. All metrics are calculated using the text exactly as provided in the ChatbotResponseText column.**\n",
        "\n",
        "## Input file\n",
        "\n",
        "The input Excel file should be saved in this folder:\n",
        "\n",
        "`Desktop/General_Programing_Python/`\n",
        "\n",
        "and named:\n",
        "\n",
        "`your_chatbot_dataset.xlsx`\n",
        "\n",
        "## Required columns\n",
        "\n",
        "The Excel file must contain these columns:\n",
        "\n",
        "- `ChatbotResponseText` - the chatbot response (text will be used exactly as-is)\n",
        "- `ScenarioID`\n",
        "- `BlindedResponseID`\n",
        "- `ChatBot`\n",
        "\n",
        "## Metrics calculated\n",
        "\n",
        "For each chatbot response, this notebook calculates:\n",
        "\n",
        "### Length metrics\n",
        "\n",
        "- Word count\n",
        "- Sentence count\n",
        "- Paragraph count\n",
        "- Average words per sentence\n",
        "\n",
        "### Formatting metrics based on predefined patterns/symbols\n",
        "\n",
        "- Headings: yes/no\n",
        "- Bullet points or numbered lists: yes/no\n",
        "- Stepwise instructions: yes/no\n",
        "\n",
        "### Readability metrics\n",
        "\n",
        "- Flesch Reading Ease\n",
        "- Flesch-Kincaid Grade Level\n",
        "\n",
        "## Important note\n",
        "\n",
        "**Text is used exactly as provided** - no cleaning or modification is applied. All metrics are calculated on the original ChatbotResponseText. Readability metrics describe linguistic accessibility and should not be interpreted as clinical quality, appropriateness, or safety."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "# MODIFY THIS with your actual file name\n",
        "input_filename = \"your_chatbot_dataset.xlsx\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Input file in your project folder\n",
        "input_file = Path.home() / \"Desktop\" / \"General_Programing_Python\" / input_filename\n",
        "\n",
        "# Output file in your project folder\n",
        "# IMPORTANT: This is a new file name, so your original input file will not be overwritten.\n",
        "output_filename = input_filename.replace(\".xlsx\", \"_with_metrics.xlsx\")\n",
        "output_file = Path.home() / \"Desktop\" / \"General_Programing_Python\" / output_filename\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Input file path:\")\n",
        "print(input_file)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nOutput file path:\")\n",
        "print(output_file)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. Load the Excel file\n",
        "\n",
